content.detailedDescription:
Was that a meteor? started watching the skies, it was a nice night.

was that the space station? traveled north to south in a straight line.

ithen some minutes later coming from sw to ne. it shuttered changing corse to demonstrate that it was not moving in a straight line. going around stars, at one point around a whole constellation. brightening and diming subtly.

in my mind i expressed my gratitude and thanks. it was still kind of scary.

some many more minutes pass. descending from high in the sky to the east. i think hello. it blinks. this time a much more yellow light than before. several other responces. my thinking goes erratic, while at a loss for words. i wonder if i could have scared it off. i think that may have been an answer to my fear during the first watch. as if to say not to fear it. 

i stayed outside looking for a little while longer, but decided to go in for a coffee and to write this report. i may  look for a minute later.

it was interesting to note that in the time immediately after the first watch, a bird made a short repetitive tune. i wish i could remember it. about 4 low churps ending with a high pitched one. not anything particularly special about it from regular bird songs. but given the circumstance it had a kind of signal sounding quality, like a shorter "close encounters of the third kind" melody. if nothing else, it was cool timing.
content.summary: If the space station could zig zag, brighten, dim, blink, speed up and slow down.

content.detailedDescription:
I was at my friend's house visiting. it was about 1:30am when i went out to the back patio to have a cigarette. i am a sky watcher and i had a clear view of the sky to the east. i suddenly saw two orange balls moving at a high rate of speed coming from the ese moving toward the wnw. they were below the (cloud) ceiling and made no sound at all and did not have tails nor did they leave a trail of debris as meteors do. the objects were moving so fast i lost sight of them as they passed over the house. i didn't have time to get to the front of the house to observe them any further. 
i didn't know what to think about what i had seen. the direction they came from was in the general area of cape canaveral. given that rockets and missles have fire from thrusters and generally leave a trail of some sort i didn't think the objects originated from the cape. 
i didn't have a psychic reaction to the objects. i felt like my friends would think i was a little crazy when i told them what i saw. 
i checked online for rocket launches or other things like that and found nothing. i thought it might have been some clandestine military thing but obviously couldn't verify that.
i've seen lots of things in the sky - meteors, fireballs, satellites, the iss, lots of different aircraft, but nothing, ever like what i saw that night.
i'm grateful to have (some) friends who don't think i was stoned or crazy or both.... 
i just wish i knew what it was that i saw.
content.summary: Sitting on friend's back patio & saw orange balls coming from se at high rate of speed. made no sound, left no trail (as in debris) j

content.detailedDescription: I was driving on the dirt road to a friends house and it was hovering low above the trees just past my destination. i layed eyes on it for 30 seconds but kept driving out of fear.The 2 bright blue headlights were pointed straight at me like 2 square eyes. i knew it could see me. as i got closer, the treeline blocked my view or their view thankfully. an hour or so later after darkfall, i saw the afterburners of a military fighter jet heading south.No lights on bottom or anywhere else.I calculated it to be about 150-200 feet wide. i dont know how long it sat there.
content.summary: I was driving and clearly seen it just hovering. was scared to stop for it could see me. 2 bright blue headlights

content.detailedDescription:
Filled out with witness on the phone at mufon h.Q. by field investigator l. flechtner on march 31, 2016
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
last august. in the evening, i had a weird feeling. i saw a orb light in the tree out my patio window. while i watched i saw the light change into about 30 different lights in the tree. they seemed to be fighting. i got my camera phone and started recording. while i was recording i saw a little white face in the tree with the lights.
later while looking at the video i discovered a video from august 2nd 2015 at 2:04 am.
i don't remember taking the video. the last thing i remember is sitting by the patio window at 10:pm. and then waking up in the morning in bed.

on the video it shows me recording a ship hovering over the back yard with reddish, orangeish, pinkish blinking lights. next to it is a roundish blob object which is blueish gray. 
on the video you can hear me go out side while recording, sigh, and then the video records two humanoids holding my head and the female is sticking me in 
the chest and abdomen. then she pulls something out of my mouth while he holds my head. i seem to be unconscious at the time. i don't remember anything at all.
i have six videos but couldn't load them on this web sight so i emailed them to mufon headquarters.

content.detailedDescription: Jan 9-1968 bolton::i was a newborn baby lying in a crib next to my mum,just hours old..My mum tells me that she was sat up in bed just relaxing when the room suddenly went cold..She says that a figure appeared at the door,she couldn't make out any features on the being but explained it as having an orange glow,she felt paralysed too,only able to move her eyes..The figure slowly glided over to her,bent down and kissed her on her chest..It then glided back to the door where it disappeared.The room warmed up immediately and she was no longer paralysed..This is how she told the story to me..She died of lung cancer in feb 1985..I had no idea what to make of this story until i saw one of your programmes and got a chill down my spine when i heard somebody else describe a very similar experience...I've also had missing time in my twenties..During an evening drive home from weymouth to gillingham in dorset england, i had made this journey on numerous occaisions..But this particular time i have no recollection of the journey except when i came to as i was approaching a t-junction, it felt as tho i'd been asleep and had just woken up.I was alone in the car and had no idea how i came to be where i was..I almost crashed the car...About 5 years after this event i was asleep in bed and woke up with what felt like some broken ribs on my right side..I put my hand on the affected area and felt three large lumps that had broken the skin and scabbed over..I had assumed that i'd been bitten but nothing i know could leave three wart sized lumps or give the impression of broken ribs..Furthermore i stripped the bed and found nothing that could have inflicted these wounds on me...I now feel that its important to share this information..Thank you..
content.summary: Possible abduction-possible medical tests-

content.detailedDescription: I was outside looking at the stars a little after 9:00 pm. i noticed a white light with a flashing red light to the east. i thought it was too far up to be from a tower. when i went inside to go to bed i realized i had not gotten the mail. i got my keys and went back outside. the lights in the east were gone and then i noticed a large diamond shaped object going overhead. it had a white light on each point and a flashing red light. i had my phone in my pocket so i snapped a bunch of pictures while it passed over me. it continued on a straight course to the west and out of sight. i got my mail and went inside to look at the pictures. at first they looked like blank frames, but on one i noticed a pinprick of white. i zoomed in and cropped the image. i had to do this to all of the pictures to see the object. the whole time the object appeared to me as a diamond shape, but the pictures have different appearances. i have only lived out in the country for about five months. three times i've seen what at first looked like a star in the east that then began moving  in a north to south direction and then made a sharp right turn and continued moving west. the object i saw last night seemed large and quite low, much lower than an aircraft of that size would normally be traveling. pictures taken on my phone appear smaller and farther away than in person. hope the fact that i zoomed in and cropped them doesn't mess up what you need to see.
content.summary: Object looked diamond shaped with a white light on each point and a red flashing light. the pictures show other shapes than what i observed

content.detailedDescription:
From my home located on the north end of the city of keizer, oregon, just north of salem, i saw what appeared at first to be a multi-colored star. while outside gazing at the few stars, which i do periodically on a clear night, i felt it was located at about 1,000-2,000 feet agl across the willamette river west of downtown salem near or above west salem. that is w-sw of my home.

as i watched it and noted its bigger size compared to other stars, i saw many colors changing on its surface. i had seen one stationary star/planet hundreds times over many years with that appearance, but now i could see that this one moved slowly in short smooth motions in various directions. that motion gave it away. i thought something may be skewing my line of site as i lost sight of it once, so i moved a little to ensure my view wasn't being blocked. it wasn't. the object was slowly moving around, but not like a hovering helicopter or an aircraft.

i got my binoculars from inside the house and saw the object had moved a little more but was acting in a similar fashion. i brought the binoculars to my eyes to improve my view and it moved slowly up to the right. i pulled the binoculars down and then it slowly went dark with no quick movements in any direction. there were no clouds in the sky.

having never reported a ufo, this time i felt it was important to report it.  previously i'd seen something like this a few times over the years and dismissed it. 

my question is has anyone else in this area reported what i saw tonight?

i feel we're not the only inhabited planet in any universe, and that too much evidence exists to in downplay or deny that earth has been visited by ufos for decades if not hundreds of years.  as a retired air force/air national guard officer (non-flyer) i have 2 former military colleagues who have each seen a ufo... on and near the ground in england (1980) and airborne over redmond, oregon (1958 or 59). both sightings have been previously documented. neither man would confirm what they saw but didn't deny that something "may have happened."
content.summary: Saw a glowing, mutli-colored star-like object hovering 5-7 miles away in clear skies over west salem at 1,000-1,500 feet. it appeared to be a big star

content.detailedDescription:
i live in a small country town in western australia. on the 8th of may 2015  i was travelling west along a country road on my to work. either side of the road way is farmers paddocks, scrub and trees. it was dark. at about 6.30pm off in the distance in a paddock to my left front (south side) i saw what i thought was a ring of fire in a paddock. i didnt think much of it at the time as i thought it could be  a farmer burning off.  it initially looked like individual flames set a distance apart in a large circle. they were orange and red in colour and appear to be pulsating.  as i got closer i slowed my vehicle down for a better look. my vehicle was now travelling at walking speed. i could not see the hull of the craft. i could only see pulsating red and orange lights that were rotating around the craft in a clockwise direction. it appeared to be about 30m in diameter and was in a stationary position in the paddock like it had landed. i was both shocked and excited at this time. i then thought to myself ill get my phone out of my top shirt pocket and take a picture so i could examine it later and make sure it was not my imagination. as soon as i thought of the camera and looked down to get it out of my pocket the light/craft disappeared?  i could not stop and investigate it any further as i was on my way to work. (nightshift).

i was a police officer for 19 yrs so i was a trained observer and not easily shaken.  this shook me up as it was the 1st time ive seen something like this.
content.summary: Observed stationary ufo in paddock at night

content.detailedDescription: Though i viewed it eastward from i-40 near griffith road exit south of kingman az , it appeared to be quite some distance away . it was a very massive triangular object about 3 full moons wide with an orange light pattern 3 to a side over an adjacent mountain range east of me ( peacock mountains ) about 25 miles away . it hovered and though i could only see it for its lights at its considerable distance i watched it start to twist axially and very slowly as the lights moved perfectly together . it was then that i realized these lights were attached to one large triangular body . then it accelerated away slightly upward and away from me in an eastward direction at a rate of acceleration that i know no human or animal could withstand that kind of g force . though this was a long time ago and my dates now are a little unsure , it was 1993 late spring and i remember this bizarre event vividly . i told a few friends but they didn't make much of it . then a about a decade later , 2003 a local news cast did a spot on triangular lighted objects back in 1997 near phoenix which is about 200 miles from here . i felt stunned but redeemed because i knew there was indeed something connective to what i had seen 4 years earlier . i still feel a bit spooked and chilled remembering how it was to see that alone at night deep out in that big dark desert .Just very weird experience .
content.summary: Traingular light pattern , extremely large , hovered while slowly turning axially then accelerated away upward very quickley .

content.detailedDescription:
Was outside on roof terrace (8th floor) of hyatt house downtown seattle, right next to space needle, with 4 friends, preparing for dinner. mostly clear skies (a few clouds toward horizon, nothing above), just about/after sunset, sky still bluish but fading (getting dark).

as i looked toward space needle, saw what first seemed like a fast jet coming from the east, heading due west (toward puget sound), slightly to the north of us. not a sound (throughout sighting). had 2 white blinking lights  (pulsating in unison at approximately 1 hz), as if each wing (l/r) had big white light covering most of wing surface, but could not discern forward fuselage or tail, hence looked like it was a flying straight wing. still thought it could be airplane despite unusual white lights pattern (am familiar with airplanes; am engineer working in aerospace) and soundless (thought it might be much higher than it seemed); for instance despite white lights flashing, thought they could still be landing lights.

object flew in straight line while displaying white pulsating lights, very fast but at perceived constant linear speed, as it subtended an angle of approximately 45 degrees from my viewpoint and initial spotting. covered this angle in not more than 10 seconds. given estimated altitude of twice the height of the space needle or more, that would still be very fast for a soundless flight; much too fast for a small drone, or for a helicopter if higher in altitude (yet could not be high enough to be soundless, which would have meant extremely fast).

mentioned helicopter because object came to a complete stop in less than one second, almost right after passing past space needle which occulted it for 3-4 seconds. remained stationary for about 5 seconds, then made in about 2 seconds a lateral translation equivalent to about 1.5 times angle subtended by top circular portion of space needle, at 90 degrees from original flightpath, i.E. toward south; stopped again. very fast acceleration & deceleration in all moves. then started displaying characteristic red/green position lights pattern and proceeded east in somewhat arced trajectory until losthe from sight within 10-15 seconds. happened too fast to get colleagues to also witness sightning, when i brought it to their attention colleague nearest to me didn't succeed in spotting it despite my pointing toward it, as it quickly became difficult evendors for me to track. complete loss of sight by the time it had covered another approximately 30 degrees in direction of puget sound.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Right above space needle, came in straight line 2 white blinking lights, stopped/hovered, lateral translation then curved path to disappearance, never a sound

content.detailedDescription:
I was volunteering at a track meet and our team was just finishing cleaning up. then 3 of us saw two orange orbs appear northwest of where we were. the orbs sat there for at least 20 minutes i did not see them leave but when i came out of a building they were gone. i then was picked up by my mom to take me home. which is when a white-green orb appeared and it sat there for another 10 minutes when the other two orange orbs appeared again together all three orbs formed a huge triangle in the night sky. that shape was made for three minutes when one of the orange orbs veerd to the right and then disappeared. now at this time it's about 8:30 at night, only the green-white orb remained when me and my mom entered our neighborhood and got home,we walked outside and saw the second orange orb also veer to the right and disappear. while this was happening is was thinking to myself i have never seen something like this before,this is crazy and somewhat creepy. the last orb, which was the green-white orb remained stationary until about 8:55 at night. which then it began to dim very slowly so i went to go get my dad and show him before it left and by the time i got back out the last orb had disappeared




note: the video provided is while i was in the car with my mom and the two orange orbs had not reappeared
content.summary: Two big orange orbs were found in night sky around 8 pm disappears then greenish whitesh orb showed up along with two orange orbs then orange orbs left and green-white orb dimmed and disappeared

content.detailedDescription:
My 16 yr. old son and i were driving just outside eagle river towards anchorage when two yellow orbs with extremely bright red lights on top flew across the highway in front of our car. they flew the length of a military rifle range. there they joined a dozen or so other orbs, all flying up and down over a specific area  at the back of the rifle range.As we drove by suddenly an unbelievable amount of gun fire erupted. the orbs were unaffected by the gun fire. 
on our way back to eagle river from anchorage we saw several men in suits standing along the highway where the orbs had cross the highway in front of our car. my son and i both forgot about the incident for a week and then both of us suddenly remembered.
content.summary: Orbs of light right in front of the car.

content.detailedDescription: On saturday march 26, 2016- i was exiting the huntington metro garage on the huntington ave side (lower huntington metro)when coming down the ramp across from fenwick dr. when i glanced up and saw a strange silver/grey object hovering off in the distance seemingly over the area of the highway/eisenhower ave/ duke st. i could not tell its exact size but it was large and stationary ( it did not lower or raised as i watched it). i noticed that the sky was partly cloudy but the top of the object was reflecting sunlight or radiated its own light. as i was watching the item, a couple came up to me and said that they had first spotted the object form the metro train as they came into eisenhower station. the wife stated that her husband did not see any type of tether and ask me did i see one. i said i did not as we watched it hover, then spin on its axis and i saw the attachment just under its "nose". it was slightly curve and reddish in color. i took out my cell phone and snap off a couple of pictures. i then quickly cross huntington ave and made my way towards huntington park, which took me know more than 5 minutes. i lost sight of the object so i crossed the length of the park still not spotting it. i made my way to the banks of camron run/ huntington creek, looked and saw nothing. i stood there for about 10 minutes before i left and went on my way. the pictures are nice and clear but the object to far away for the phone to get a better picture. blow-up you can see the attachment better.
content.summary: Silver-grey oval/egg shape ufo over alexandria, va

content.detailedDescription:
Was outside between 9-10 pm looking south.  what i thought was one of the stars in orion began to move across the sky. it moved upward in an arc to the left, toward the northeast sky. when it was in the northeast, appearing near jupiter its direction changed from a continued arc to more of a descension.  it descended and was out of sight. there seemed to be a glow coming from that area in the distance afterwards.  at first i thought it might be the light of the moon commencing to rise but the moon did not rise for several more hours.  heard dogs barking in the distance.  seemed like it would have been miles away.  it appeared like a bright star or like jupiter or venus appear. it moved much faster than a plane.  whole event occurred in 5-7 seconds.  
my family had a very close encounter in 1973 with an object that hovered directly over our car (after my dad pulled off the road to watch it).  the 1973 object moved quickly and even stopped in midair and reversed its direction. the starlike object's movement reminded me of the 1973 object.
content.summary: Star-like object arced across sky then descended

content.detailedDescription: Was leaving doherty's pub after i ate lunch(was not drinking)and looked up to see what i first thought was a flock of geese in a v-formation. the 15-20 objects were traveling from south to north. they first appeared white and black yet somehow partly transparent with small wings. the v-formation suddenly broke up and the objects grouped together in a circular formation. i then called a parking enforcement lady(meter maid) over and pointed the objects out to her. another man smoking behind an office building was observing them also. by this time the objects appeared as metallic or chrome orbs. they then started swirling like leaves in a whirlwind while moving to the west, away from us. the sky was clear and the sun seemed to reflect off of the objects in many different colors, one color at a time - very bright, almost star-like. the objects then appeared to turn the exact color of the blue sky or maybe became invisible. the meter maid and i looked at each other and were speechless. i felt as though the objects knew i was watching them and that they wanted to be seen by me.
content.summary: 15-20 white/black/transparent objects in v-formation
